Troubleshooting Tips
Issue: Cribl won't start
# Check if port 9000 is already in use
sudo netstat -tlnp | grep 9000

# Check Cribl logs
tail -f /opt/cribl/log/cribl.log

# Verify permissions
ls -la /opt/cribl
Issue: Regex patterns not matching
# Test regex patterns independently
import re
pattern = r'YOUR_PATTERN'
test_line = "YOUR_LOG_LINE"
match = re.match(pattern, test_line)
print(match.groupdict() if match else "No match")
Issue: API calls failing
# Verify Cribl API is accessible
curl -v http://localhost:9000/api/v1/system/info

# Check authentication requirements
# Default: no auth required for local access

# Enable debug logging in Python
import logging
logging.basicConfig(level=logging.DEBUG)
Issue: Logs not being enriched
Verify input file paths are correct
Check parser regex patterns match log format
Ensure output directory exists and is writable
Review Cribl pipeline configuration in web UI
Check for parsing errors in logs
